.H 2 "defined"
This function requires a single argument,
the name of a variable to be tested for existence.
It returns "1" (true) if the named variable is defined and "" (false) if it
is not.
.H 3 "Example"
This function is most often seen in conditional portions of cookbooks:
.eB
if [defined baseline] then
        cc_flags = [cc_flags] -I[baseline];
.eE
